main event: Observers in Duluth and Floodwood, Minnesota witnessed a bullet, tear drop cylinder shaped object, white in color, with blinking lights, descending overhead at a 35-45 degree angle.
interesting points: The observed object was estimated to be about 100 feet long., The object exhibited a variety of colors including blue, orange, red, white, and bluish green., Witnesses reported that the object was silent and appeared to be on fire., The sighting lasted between 5 to 15 seconds., The object was last seen burning out and falling into a swamp.
sighted object: bullet, tear drop cylinder shaped object
witness description: Civilians including a steel worker, a station agent, and a highway patrolman.
